On 8/16/2016 at 4:34 PM, Siege said:

In case no one was aware but might care, EVE isn't being listed in CKAN currently because the version available to the repository says it's only compatible with 1.1.2.

For convenience, I have one in my personal CKAN repository (CKAN | Settings | CKAN Settings | New | https://github.com/rkagerer/KSP-Fwiffo-Repository/raw/master/CKAN-meta-fwiffo.zip | OK).

Can't remember exactly whether/how I mutated the default package, but I've been using this one in 1.1.3 for ages without problems.  It still points to EVE 1.1-1.  I'll look into the May 1.1-3 release...

Nevermind, not needed.  StockVisualEnhancements is already marked 1.1.3-compatible in CKAN and appears to include the latest EVE stuff.

Edited September 13, 2016 by Fwiffo

@rbray89: Just checked it on 1.2. 
BROKEN.

@Waz would you be able to create a patch for this to update to 1.2 (once it actually drops) in rbray's absence? I know you were fiddling with the mod before so I don't know if you'd be able to patch it to work with 1.2 or not?

I've been wondering for a while now - did rbray ever say he was leaving for an indefinite amount of time? Or did he just soar off into the sunset? I don't recall ever seeing anything posted here but I know he's been in chat rooms...

@Nhawks17 - no promises, but I'm giving it a go. I managed to bodge kOS into working sufficiently for my purposes and the only real problem was the fuel flow code, which changed in 1.2, so not surprising. There isn't anything Squad have mentioned in 1.2 that will obviously break EVE, but it's a pretty big mod, so I'm certain problems will show up. Ping me if I haven't given a progress report in the next day or so. Are we certain @rbray89 is out-of-the-picture - he's seemed active in other forums - I was hoping to get some info on how the volume clouds works so as to improve performance. :-(

I've already emailed him like 3 days ago.  I haven't received and answer back yet though.  I'm sure he knows 1.2 is in prerelease as he has been on other forums.  I don't necessarily want to jump the gun on an update but if he is planning on  taking a longer break than what he has already taken,  perhaps we should look to fork it.  @Waz I'm am hoping you have some success with performance issues.  That is the single biggest complaint I get with my visual packs.

Okay, here's my first working build:

https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B_FliOxI5-THR19Oam40dlkwazA?usp=sharing

Not tested much, and only with the BoulderCo configs.

Main thing was getting the old broken shaders working and moving the shaders to AssetBundles.
Thank you Waz for continuing the work on this most crucial mod. Happy day for the entire community.

Aparently everything is where it's supossed to be:

GameData/EnviromentalVisualEnhancements  ->for yor build

GameData/BoulderCo  -> Oficial Release configs and textures.

As far as I know, There is no need of module manager, Right?

So, I ported old EVE 7.4 to 1.2 prerelease. I can say, thats simple recompiling plugin not enough, you also need to create assetbundle with shaders in Unity and load it into game. My code: 

private static bool BundleLoaded = false;
private static Dictionary<string, Shader> LoadedShaders = new Dictionary<string, Shader>();

public static void LoadBundle()
{
    if (BundleLoaded)
        return;

    using (WWW www = new WWW("file://" + KSPUtil.ApplicationRootPath + "GameData/ExamplePlugin/Shaders.bundle"))
    {
        if (www.error != null)
            Log("Shaders bundle not found!");

        AssetBundle bundle = www.assetBundle;
        Shader[] shaders = bundle.LoadAllAssets<Shader>();

        foreach (Shader shader in shaders)
        {
            Log("Shader " + shader.name + " is loaded");
            LoadedShaders.Add(shader.name, shader);
        }

        bundle.Unload(false);
        www.Dispose();

        BundleLoaded = true;
    }
}

public static Shader LoadShader(string name)
{
    if (LoadedShaders.ContainsKey(name))
        return LoadedShaders[name];

    Debug.Log("Shader " + name + " not found!");
    return Shader.Find("Hidden/InternalErrorShader");
}
